The Australian government has givensupport in principle to the production of platinum and silverbullion coins at the Perth Mint, Treasurer Paul Keating said.    This followed the success of the Australian Nugget goldbullion coins launched this year, he said in a statement.    He said that, as with the Australian nuggets, the coinswould be legal tender. The platinum coins would be made in fourweights but the silver coin would be of one ounce weight.    He said detailed arrangements for their issue would befinalised after talks between the Federal authorities and theWestern Australian government, owner of the Perth Mint. REUTER&#3;